history.text: Hi, what did you think of the movie Frozen?  I loved it!
I also enjoyed it.
Did you like the singing?  I thought Anna's voice was really good.
Yes, I did like the singing.
Elsa's voice was also good.
Yes, she had a beautiful voice, and the best song to sing.
I read The Snow Queen years ago, and really liked it.
I never read that, but I probably should
It was good. I liked it.
I agree with the critics, it was the best disney musical in a long time.
Agreed! We listened to many of the songs over and over again.
I had no idea ice superpowers was called cryokinetic magic.
Right! I didn't either.
I don't get why they had to remove the memories from Anna. Couldn't they have just explained to her what happened?
I thought Elsa's parents went about hiding her powers all wrong.  they should have tried teaching her control, not suppress it.
exactly!
typical disney movie to kill off the parents!
Typical. Parents get in the way. Hijinks can't ensue if there are parents around to say "That's a bad idea"
my mom's favorite line "no more shenanigans!"
Han's was such a jerk!
Like, if there had been a dad or mom here they would have said, "Everybody calm down. There are no monsters here."
yes, he was!
I can't believe Anna fell for his antics
I can. It's the first person her own age she's seen in years who is actually interested in her.
hm, i suppose that's true.  she needed more playdates growing up.
She had no friends after her parents died the only people she saw were the servants and Elsa.
I always wondered what happened to Kristoff's parents.
And why did he have a reindeer? What happened to Sven's parents?
you'd think the servants would have kids.  oh well.  at least eventually she gets olaf back.  yeah, they never did give him a decent back story
kristoff, raised by troll people!
I would think the servants would have kids. But it definitely shows Anna always being alone and longing for Elsa to play with her.
Kristoff races her back to Hans, even though he's fallen in love with her himself.
yup, it's a great movie about sisterly love, but you can't dig too deep into the storyline!
exactly.
